<strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> Pre-delay under 20ms = intimate/small room. 20–50ms = medium hall. 50–100ms = large space. Above 100ms you start to hear a distinct echo. Set pre-delay to roughly 1ms per meter of perceived space. <strong>Formula:</strong> d = (t × 343) ÷ 2
  </div>
</section>
