<h2 class="section-title hidden stagger-1">RT60 Physics Lab</h2>
<p class="section-desc hidden stagger-2">RT60 is the time required for a sound to decay by 60 decibels after its source stops. Sabine's formula (1900) links room volume, surface area, and absorption coefficient to predict RT60. Adjust the parameters to see how the decay curve changes.</p>
